# Paired Benchmark

This folder contains the scripts, latent representations, benchmark results and figure-generation code for the fully paired PBMC RNA-ATAC integration benchmark.

In the fully paired setting, every cell contains both RNA and ATAC measurements. This represents the best-case condition for multi-omics integration and was used to evaluate whether different methods can preserve biological cell-type structure when complete multi-omic information is available.

## Overview

This benchmark compares three multi-omics integration methods:

- **MultiVI**
- **GLUE**
- **MOFA+**

The benchmark focuses mainly on biological conservation and clustering agreement in the integrated latent space. The same marker-based PBMC cell-type annotation was used across all methods to ensure consistent comparison.

